sentence: Ian Tamblyn (born December 2, 1947) is a Canadian folk music singer-songwriter and record producer, adventurer, and playwright.
In 1976 he released his full-length debut album, Ian Tamblyn, which won a Juno Award for Best Album Cover that year.
In 2008 Tamblyn, along with Bruce Cockburn and other Canadian folk artists released Dancing Alone, a two CD tribute album of the songs of influential Canadian songwriter and poet William Hawkins.
